      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(discord): preserve newlines across chunk boundaries",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\n`chunkDiscordText` in `extensions/discord/src/chunk.ts` drops the newline separator when it flushes a chunk at a line boundary. As a result, the text that follows an inline error line can appear truncated or merged into the previous chunk, changing the message content that Discord users see.\n\nFixes #96007\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nThe chunker now tracks whether the next chunk starts with a leading newline and reserves one line/character of budget for that newline. This ensures that when chunks are joined back together, the original text is reproduced exactly, including line breaks after error lines.\n\n## User Impact\n\nDiscord messages that contain inline error text followed by more content will no longer have their subsequent content truncated or glued to the error line.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- Updated `extensions/discord/src/chunk.test.ts` with a regression test covering the newline-across-boundary case.\n- Adjusted `durable-delivery.test.ts` and `outbound-adapter.test.ts` expectations to match the preserved newline behavior.\n- All Discord extension tests pass locally.\n\n## AI Code Generation Disclosure\n\nThis patch was generated and reviewed with assistance from an AI coding agent. The change, tests, and PR description were produced as part of an automated GitHub issue resolution workflow.",
